Exam Preparation Advice
Choose a Date
The first step I took before beginning exam preparation was to commit to a specific date for the exam. You must choose a date to push yourself to prepare seriously; otherwise, you will fall into a cycle of procrastination.

Prepare Your Room the Day Before the Exam
Prepare your room by ensuring your desk is clean and free of devices or papers that you used during your revision. Test your internet connection and download the PSI browser to verify that your laptop is compatible with it (sometimes recent Windows updates can break the PSI exam launcher). Do not forget to place your valid ID in a location where you can easily find it the next day. You will need this document, and you do not want to be rushing to find a missing ID at the last minute like I did.

Daily Routine
Throughout the preparation period, I followed a one-lab-per-day strategy. This allowed me to maintain focus on daily objectives and become proficient in using the command line throughout the entire preparation period, which let me to approach the exam with confidence.

Equipment Requirements
Only one monitor is allowed during the exam. No devices or papers are allowed on your desk.

During the Exam
When taking the exam, breathe and stay calm. This is not the hardest exam in your life. Be sure to read the questions carefully and pay attention to the current node to verify that you are on the right node and cluster. Sometimes you may need to change contexts within the same cluster.

Flag the more difficult questions and do not spend too much time on them. This is a race against time, and you must maximize your points to succeed by answering all questions.

Be an expert with VIM üôÇ
Mastering Vim significantly enhances productivity and efficiency for developers and system administrators by enabling rapid text editing through keyboard shortcuts, reducing dependency on the mouse, and facilitating seamless workflow integration across various Unix-based environments.

Tip: during the exam, name your manifests with the number of question.yaml and put every object you want to create under the same manifest, it will help you gain time when troubleshooting problems.

Do not forget to apply your manifestsüòÖ

My overall thoughts of the experience
It was a good and fulfilling experience where I got to learn about new aspects of administrating Kubernetes clusters.

